STAGE 100 P0-011: MarkdownRenderer.jsx URL linkify

FIND (around line 78-82):
  var processed = useMemo(function() {
    if (!content) return '';
    return autoLinkSparse(content, maxAutoLinks);
  }, [content, maxAutoLinks]);

REPLACE WITH:
  var processed = useMemo(function() {
    if (!content) return '';
    var linked = autoLinkSparse(content, maxAutoLinks);
    // STAGE_100: linkify bare URLs not already in markdown link syntax
    linked = linked.replace(
      /(?<!\]\()(?<!\[)(https?:\/\/[^\s<)\]]+)/g,
      '[$1]($1)'
    );
    return linked;
  }, [content, maxAutoLinks]);

HOW IT WORKS:
- Negative lookbehinds (?<!]\() and (?<!\[) skip URLs already in [text](url)
- Bare URLs become [https://example.com](https://example.com)
- ReactMarkdown renders them as <a> via existing components.a handler
- External links get target=_blank from existing safeHref logic
- No new dependencies required
